meanings.definition: Print (additional text or images) over existing material.
meanings.sent1: She overprinted her name on the letter.
meanings.sent2: The company decided to overprint the logo on the packaging.
meanings.sent3: The teacher accidentally overprinted the assignment instructions on top of the student's answers.
meanings.sent4: The rain overprinted the sidewalk with muddy footprints.
meanings.sent5: The artist carefully overprinted the colors to create a beautiful blend.

meanings.definition: The process of printing additional material on top of existing material.
meanings.sent1: The overprinting of the brochure made it more informative.
meanings.sent2: The book had a unique design due to the overprinting of illustrations.
meanings.sent3: The overprinting of the menu caused confusion among the customers.
meanings.sent4: The overprinting of memories on the old photograph brought back nostalgia.
meanings.sent5: The overprinting of patterns on the fabric added depth to the design.
